================================================================================
                        HEALTHCARE DATA DISCLAIMER
================================================================================

This software, including all code examples, compliance checklists, monitoring
templates, and documentation, is provided for EDUCATIONAL AND DEMONSTRATION
PURPOSES ONLY.

BEFORE USING IN A PRODUCTION HEALTHCARE ENVIRONMENT:

1. SECURITY REVIEW
   - Conduct a thorough security assessment by qualified professionals
   - Perform penetration testing by certified security experts
   - Review all code for vulnerabilities specific to your environment

2. COMPLIANCE VERIFICATION
   - HIPAA: Ensure compliance with 45 CFR Part 164 (Security Rule)
   - GDPR: Verify compliance with EU General Data Protection Regulation
   - Local regulations: Check jurisdiction-specific healthcare data laws
   - Obtain sign-off from your compliance and legal teams

3. PROFESSIONAL REVIEW
   - Have licensed healthcare IT professionals review implementations
   - Consult with healthcare security specialists
   - Engage qualified legal counsel for regulatory matters

4. TESTING REQUIREMENTS
   - Never use real PHI (Protected Health Information) in testing
   - Use synthetic or de-identified data for all development
   - Conduct User Acceptance Testing with stakeholders

5. PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT
   - Follow your organization's change management procedures
   - Implement proper monitoring and incident response
   - Maintain audit logs per regulatory requirements (6 years for HIPAA)

